gomodel:SYNGO_4530  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 3B shows accumulation of immunoreactivity (immunoperoxidase product) in presynaptic boutons of axodendritic and axospinous synapses in the human cerebral cortex. Fig. 3C-F show examples of immunogold particles associated with vesicles along the presynaptic membrane lining the synaptic cleft. As neurotrypsin contains a signal peptide in is a secreted protein, it is assumed that it is localized within vesicles at the active zone. Caveat: it is unclear whether these are clear synaptic vesicles or dense-core vesicles or rather undefined vesicle-like organelles.\nAffinity-purified antibodies raised against its proteolytic domain were used for specific neurotrypsin detection (as stated on p. 1780).. Experimental description: Fig. 3. Immunolocalization of neurotrypsin.\nNeurotrypsin was visualized in adult human cerebral cortex... (p. 1781)" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" ;
        dc:date           "2021-05-17" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4530" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

